<node TEXT="hotkeys" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_405342184" CREATED="1681498384497" MODIFIED="1681498389780">
<node TEXT="CTRL-M : (Mute) Enables / Disables GPLMotec keyboard shortcuts.&#xa;&#xa;&#xa;&#xa;CTRL-SPACEBAR : Place GPLMotec on screen N&#xb0;2. The forced maintenance of the software on screen N&#xb0;2 is automatic, but I kept&#xa;this keyboard shortcut, because originally it had to be done manually.&#xa;&#xa;&#xa;&#xa;SHIFT-TAB : Successively switches between the display modules of the &quot;Motec-Sim&quot; window&#xa;&#xa;&#xa;&#xa;CTRL-TAB : Switch successively between the technical modules on the right of the screen.&#xa;&#xa;&#xa;&#xa;CTRL-A : Toggles between real-time display or Average tire temperature.&#xa;&#xa;&#xa;&#xa;CTRL-R : Resetting the lap time counting system. This will be done automatically if SHIFT-R is detected.&#xa;&#xa;&#xa;&#xa;CTRL-L : ON / OFF logging for GP&#xb2;L (see the LOG folder in GPLMotec folder). If ON : LED is red in MotecSim module.&#xa;&#xa;CTRL-N: (Next) when in practice mode at Nurburgring track, press CTRL-TAB, you will see a Nurburgring module to jum at different track zones to practice.  CTRL-N for next zone&#xa;&#xa;CTRL-T : (Temp) Works only if you are in the average temperature mode (CTRL-A, the &quot;Avg&quot; checkbox is set in the tire temperature&#xa;module). Successively switches to different tire temperature recording modes.&#xa;&#xa;TURN RIGHT: Friction temperatures on the surface of the tires will ONLY be read when the car is turning right, this is detected by&#xa;GForce.&#xa;&#xa;TURN LEFT: Friction temperatures on the surface of the tires will ONLY be read when the car is turning left, this is detected by&#xa;GForce.&#xa;&#xa;TURN RIGHT and LEFT: Friction temperatures on the surface of the tires read when in all turns.&#xa;&#xa;POWER: Friction temperatures on the surface of the tires read only when the engine power is high on the rear wheels, including&#xa;when cornering, but never when braking." ID="ID_952174895" CREATED="1681498391812" MODIFIED="1681498977986"/>
<node TEXT="setup page" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_881273230" CREATED="1681498521122" MODIFIED="1681498525741">
<node TEXT="NOTE: You will not see the modifications in real time on the game screen, but when you exit the game setup page by clicking the&#xa;green button: your modification will be saved in the setup file.&#xa;&#xa;&#xa;&#xa;CTRL-K : (Kpa) Activates the tire pressure fine adjustment mode. You will see a red label appear on the tire affected by the&#xa;modification. To go to the next tire: press TAB. To change the pressure, press + or - on the numeric keypad. Remember to exit fine&#xa;tune mode when you are done (CTRL-K again).&#xa;&#xa;&#xa;&#xa;CTRL-C : (Camber) Activates the camber fine adjustment mode. You will see a red label appear on the tire affected by the&#xa;modification. To go to the next tire: press TAB. To change the camber angle, press + or - on the numeric keypad. Remember to exit&#xa;fine tune mode when you are done (CTRL-C again).&#xa;&#xa;&#xa;&#xa;CTRL-D : (Differencial)&#xa;(Before that, type CTRL-TAB to see the Differencial module)&#xa;&#xa;Activates the Diff Angle fine adjustement (5 by 5). Press TAB to go on the next label (power / coast / disk), type + or - to change&#xa;value. Remember to exit fine tune mode when you are done (CTRL-D again).&#xa;&#xa;&#xa;&#xa;CTRL-G : (Gearbox)&#xa;&#xa;(Before that, type CTRL-TAB to see the Gearbox module)&#xa;&#xa;Activates the Gearbox ration fine adjustement. Presse TAB to go on next gear (6 will by gray except for BRM), type + or - to&#xa;increase / decrease value. The basic setting must first be done in the game. Here it is only for fine tuning.&#xa;&#xa;Remember to exit fine tune mode when you are done (CTRL-G again)." ID="ID_884117947" CREATED="1681498527461" MODIFIED="1681498570674"/>
</node>
<node TEXT="CTRL-N: (Next) when in practice mode at Nurburgring track, press CTRL-TAB, you will see a Nurburgring module to jum at different track zones to practice.  CTRL-N for next zone" ID="ID_1961922692" CREATED="1681499007511" MODIFIED="1681499014725"/>
</node>
